<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203>
    dc:creator "Ascher, John S.", "Kasparek, Max", "Nalinrachatakan, Pakorn", "Thanoosing, Chawatat", "Traiyasut, Prapun", "Warrit, Natapot" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A review of the anthidiine bees (Apoidea, Megachilidae) in Thailand" ;
    bibo:endPage "284" ;
    bibo:journal "ZooKeys" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-19" ;
    bibo:startPage "235" ;
    bibo:volume "1186" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure6>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure7>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure8> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Eoanthidium (Hemidiellum) riparium (Cockerell, 1929). Female holotype of Dianthidium riparium Cockerell, 1929 (syn.) from Thailand (A, B). Male from Thailand (BSRU-AB- 4360) (C, D). Female from Laos (BMNH-ENT- 2017 - 196 (ACQ )) (E), Female from Laos (BSRU-AA- 1224) (F), male from Laos (BSRU-AA- 1236) (G-K), and male from Thailand (BSRU-AB- 4358) (L) H-J male genitalia in dorsal, ventral, and lateral view K male S 8 L apical sterna of male in ventral view. Scale bars: 2 mm (D); 1 mm (A-C, E-G); 0.5 mm (H-L)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/954860" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Illustration of Eoanthidium (Hemidiellum) riparium (Cockerell, 1929) facial maculation mapped according to their geographic locations (blue boxes indicate Indian-Pakistani morphs, reddish boxes indicate Indochina morphs; a morph marked with asterisk is illustrated based on Wu 1962: fig. 22)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/954861" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1186.95203.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Male of Eoanthidium riparium (Cockerell, 1929) from different regions A-C dorsal view of individuals from South India (Karnakata), Pakistan (Panjab), and North India (Hisar, Haryana) respectively D face of a male Eoanthidium riparium from Pakistan (SEMC 27). Note the change in the ground color from black (A) across reddish brown on terga and black on scutum (B) to entirely reddish brown (C). Also, note the shape of the reddish apical margin of the clypeus (black arrows) which is similar to the drawing of Gupta (1993: fig. 65) for Eo. punjabense." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/954862" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

